  ],
  "status": "published",
  "updatedAt": "2026-03-19T00:00:00.000Z",
  "content": {
    "version": 1,
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "id": "block-1",
        "level": 1,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Codex Is Good At"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Codex works best when the task has a clear tool boundary and a concrete output, instead of free-form edits across raw JSON files."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-3",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In Anydocs, good Codex tasks include:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "id": "block-4",
        "style": "bulleted",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "element-4-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "validating the project contract and enabled languages"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-5-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "finding pages by page id or slug"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-6-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "creating and updating pages"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-7-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "changing page status in a controlled way"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-8-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "checking navigation and page state before and after changes"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-9",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The main rule is simple: **have Codex call MCP tools instead of guessing the source-file layout and editing JSON directly.**"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
